                				<h4><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/10/17/to-restore-confidence-in-economy-a-test-of-europes-banks/?ref=dealbook">Regulators Are Gauging Europeâs Banks, and Remedy May Sting a Little</a></h4>
				<p class="nyt-article-byline">By JACK EWING and LANDON THOMAS JR.</p>
				<p class="nyt-article-summary">Echoing a U.S. move from 2009, the European Central Bank is taking a hard look at banksâ books, but its findings may further rattle the markets.</p>
